@garfield
check this link
http://support.apple.com/kb/TS1888

..and try first 
Clear the QMaster cache

You can sometimes resolve issues with batch processing by clearing the QMaster cache.

Quit Compressor and Batch Monitor.
In the Finder choose Go > Go to Folder.
In the dialog that appears, type the following path: /var/spool/qmaster/
Click Go.
Drag the contents of /var/spool/qmaster/ to the trash.
Restart your computer.
Repair File Permissions
Close all the files and applications that you have open.
Open Disk Utility (located in the Utilities folder in Applications) and select your startup disk in the list on the left.
Click First Aid.
Click the Repair Disk Permissions button.
..if not helps, try reinstall and other points on this link.
